  <source>University of Aarhus</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Remote ischemic conditioning (RIC) is a therapeutic strategy for protecting organs or tissue
      against the detrimental effects of acute ischemia-reperfusion injury. It remains unknown
      whether this can be used in retinal vascular occlusive diseases. The purpose of the present
      study is to examine whether the autoregulation of retinal vessel diameters in normal persons
      change after remote ischemic conditioning.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
